HANTAVIRUS UPDATE 2010 - AMERICAS (03): USA (COLORADO)
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Thu 28 Jan 2010
Source: The Denver Post, The Pueblo Chieftain/Associated Press (AP)
report [edited]
<http://www.denverpost.com/breakingnews/ci_14285686>


A virus carried by deer mice is being blamed for the death of an
Alamosa County person. The Alamosa County Health Department says [a]
hantavirus caused the death of a county resident. No details have
been given about the victim or when the person died.

Hantavirus[es] [cause] a rare disease; [the virus is] carried by deer
mice and passed to humans through dust from droppings. People can
also get [a] hantavirus [infection] by handling dead mice.

Alamosa County's last hantavirus death was in the 2007, when a
28-year-old woman died.

--
Communicated by:
HealthMap Alerts via ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The CDC MMWR Morb Mortal Wkly Rep 2009 58(50); 1409-12
<http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/mm5850a3.htm?s_cid=mm5850a3_e>
(cited in ProMED archive no. 20091223.4323) reported 2 fatal cases of
hantavirus pulmonary syndrome in children in Colorado in 2009 caused
by Sin Nombre hantavirus. The Alamosa County, Colorado case reported
above does not indicate the hantavirus involved, but Sin Nombre virus
is the most likely pathogen.

A photograph of a deer mouse (_Peromyscus maniculatus_), the main
reservoir rodent host of Sin Nombre virus, is available at
<http://www.discoverlife.org/IM/I_RB/0000/320/Peromyscus_maniculatus,I_RB26.jpg>.


Maps showing the location of the states in the western USA including
Colorado, can be accessed at
<http://www.sioux.com/images/US_MAP.gif>
and the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/r/013z>.
For a map of counties showing the location of Alamosa County in
south-central Colorado see
<http://www.mapsofworld.com/usa/states/colorado/colorado-maps/colorado-county-map.jpg>.
- Mod.TY]
